HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 989
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Matthew
McDowell on being named the Signal Mountain
Fire Department Firefighter of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should honor those
individuals who, during the course of their duties, endeavor to protect the lives of their fellow
citizens, braving great dangers and putting themselves at risk to save others; and
WHEREAS, Engineer Matthew McDowell is one such individual, who was named the
2025 Signal Mountain Fire Department Firefighter of the Year in recognition of his exemplary
service; and
WHEREAS, the Firefighter of the Year Award, which recognizes excellence, dedication,
and performance, is presented to a member selected by the fire chief who best exemplifies the
department's values, professionalism, and commitment to service; and
WHEREAS, Engineer McDowell has only been serving with the department for fifteen
months; however, during this time, he has completed Emergency Medical Responder and Basic
Emergency Medical Technician training, as well as Fire Apparatus Operator and Advanced
Extrication certifications; and
WHEREAS, Matthew McDowell is consistently among the first to volunteer for
assignments and is deeply committed to strengthening his crew through mentoring and
supporting new members; and
WHEREAS, Engineer McDowell has given selflessly in support of his department, the
fire service, and his community, and it is wholly fitting that we recognize him for his dedication to
personal excellence and his receipt of this distinguished honor; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
HJR0989
013598
- 1 -

CONCURRING, that we commend and congratulate Engineer Matthew McDowell upon being
named the 2025 Signal Mountain Fire Department Firefighter of the Year, extending our sincere
gratitude for his devoted service.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
